<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<h2 id="drivers-hours-and-tachograph-rules">Drivers’ hours and tachograph rules</h2>

<div class="call-to-action">
<h3 id="drivers-hours-and-eu-exit">Drivers’ hours and EU Exit</h3>
<p>If the UK leaves the EU without a deal, the EU drivers’ hours and tachograph rules will be kept as UK law.</p>

<p>Journeys within the UK that are currently covered by EU rules will still be covered by these rules.</p>

<p>International journeys that start or end in the UK (including to and from EU countries) will be covered by AETR rules. These match the EU rules, so it will not change what you must do to follow the rules.</p>

<p>If the UK leaves the EU without a deal, we will update the guidance documents on this page to confirm that the EU rules will be kept.</p>
</div>

<p>Check the drivers’ hours and tachograph rules for:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/drivers-hours-goods-vehicles">goods vehicles</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/drivers-hours-passenger-vehicles">buses and coaches</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>


